{"source":"user-event","type":"click","text":"A\n    \n      VLM-as-Planner (Recommended)\n      Architecture: CLIP/LLaMA-Vision receives RGB-D frame → generates a language description of the scene → LLM decides next exploration frontier in natural language → PX4 waypoint controller executes.\n      Stack: CLIP or LLaVA for perception, GPT-4V or local LLaMA-3-Vision for planning, existing PX4 waypoint API for execution.\n      Pro: Cleanest separation of concerns. Each component is independently testable. Very adaptable to ground-robot baselines (NavGPT, VoroNav). Strong story for master's apps.\n      Con: API latency if using cloud VLM. Inference speed may limit real-time use.","choice":"a","id":null,"timestamp":1781518153392}
